which means you workin'
for a straight-up punk.

243
00:15:31.014 --> 00:15:32.057
Ya feel me?

244
00:15:34.309 --> 00:15:36.269
I'm out here in these streets every day.

245
00:15:36.603 --> 00:15:37.687
Me an' my lonesome.

246
00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:40.482
An' where he at? Huh?

247
00:16:03.547 --> 00:16:05.382
Yo. y'all put it in his ear.

248
00:16:05.924 --> 00:16:09.886
Marlo Stanfield is not a man for this town.
You dig?

249
00:16:10.137 --> 00:16:11.388
Mcnulty: Mmm-hmm.

250
00:16:12.597 --> 00:16:13.807
Yeah.

251
00:16:17.477 --> 00:16:18.603
Yeah. eight men. four cars.

252
00:16:18.687 --> 00:16:21.189
Ellis briefed 'em.
They know what's what.

253
00:16:21.314 --> 00:16:22.607
Freamon: Do they still...

254
00:16:23.692 --> 00:16:25.586
No. they're just happy for the ot.
Don't worry. Lester.

255
00:16:25.610 --> 00:16:26.862
All right. then.

256
00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:33.410
Just sign the motherfucker
and shut the fuck up.

257
00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:43.253
Gimme.

258
00:16:46.423 --> 00:16:48.592
We ready?
Cause you gotta figure an extra hour

259
00:16:48.675 --> 00:16:51.094
to get round the capital beltway
this time of day.

260
00:16:54.181 --> 00:16:55.891
You ever done an FBI profile before?

261
00:16:56.099 --> 00:16:57.976
- Once.
- How'd it go?

262
00:16:59.102 --> 00:17:02.147
They take your file. read you back
some shit you already know.

263
00:17:02.814 --> 00:17:05.442
- Then why do it?
- So that we can say we did.

264
00:17:13.867 --> 00:17:17.871
Need a pack of Newport. Soft pack.

265
00:17:28.340 --> 00:17:29.901
Let me get one of them. too.

266
00:17:37.307 --> 00:17:38.308
Don't shoot!

267
00:18:02.499 --> 00:18:04.125
Lowenthal. Where the fuck is he?

268
00:18:04.209 --> 00:18:06.544
- Um. he's...
- Ah.

269
00:18:07.170 --> 00:18:08.755
There you go. bunk.

270
00:18:10.006 --> 00:18:11.466
Hey.

271
00:18:11.800 --> 00:18:16.346
request for a DNA comparison.
case 06h-271.

272
00:18:16.680 --> 00:18:18.098
Latent trace to obtained samples.

273
00:18:18.181 --> 00:18:22.686
And it's a part of the serial killer thing.
It's now a part of that investigation.

274
00:18:22.894 --> 00:18:25.689
That's different.
If it's connected to that investigation...

275
00:18:25.772 --> 00:18:27.232
It is. here.

276
00:18:28.233 --> 00:18:31.027
- It's in my notes.
- I never said I was in a firefight.

277
00:18:31.111 --> 00:18:32.862
- Not on that day.
- Sorry. but you did.

278
00:18:32.946 --> 00:18:36.199
I told you the lead vehicle took a hit
from an elevated ied.

279
00:18:36.783 --> 00:18:39.619
Killed the 50 gunner.
and blew the hands off the driver.

280
00:18:39.703 --> 00:18:42.664
That's it. That's enough. man.

281
00:18:42.747 --> 00:18:45.500
- Why make the rest of that shit up?
- I didn't make anything up.

282
00:18:45.583 --> 00:18:47.627
- We sat there having coffee.
- Coffee?

283
00:18:47.711 --> 00:18:50.046
-Having doughnuts and coffee. And you said.
-what I say?

284
00:18:50.297 --> 00:18:51.798
- Can I finish?
- I don't know.

285
00:18:52.007 --> 00:18:54.026
I'm hearing about coffee and doughnuts.
I'm not hearing...

286
00:18:54.050 --> 00:18:57.012
If you're not going to let me
tell my side of the story...

287
00:18:57.095 --> 00:18:59.723
A lie ain't a side of
the story. it's just a lie.

288
00:18:59.806 --> 00:19:03.393
- I don't have to listen to this.
- Ok. Scott. let's just relax here.

289
00:19:03.560 --> 00:19:06.021
Both you gentlemen.
let's just step back here. please?

290
00:19:06.855 --> 00:19:10.150
Now. Mr. Hanning. forgive me.
but do you drink much?

291
00:19:10.233 --> 00:19:12.235
You think I fucking sleep
under a bridge sober?

292
00:19:13.737 --> 00:19:17.699
Sometimes when I have a few.
and I do like to have a few.

293
00:19:18.575 --> 00:19:21.411
I tend to be a little more descriptive
in the telling of a tale.

294
00:19:21.494 --> 00:19:25.248
I know what it is to tell a story.
I've told plenty in my time.

295
00:19:27.876 --> 00:19:32.839
But there's some things that happen.
you don't ever fuck with them.

296
00:19:35.342 --> 00:19:36.551
Scott?

297
00:19:42.724 --> 00:19:44.017
I believe you. Mr. Hanning.

298
00:19:44.225 --> 00:19:46.561
I believe that you believe.

299
00:19:47.312 --> 00:19:49.522
That you believe you told me one thing.

300
00:19:50.482 --> 00:19:54.569
But. sir. with all due respect and gratitude.
for you and the service you gave this country.

301
00:19:54.652 --> 00:19:56.321
you didn't tell me that thing.

302
00:19:56.571 --> 00:19:59.741
You told me something else.
Iwrote what Mr. Hanning told me.

303
00:20:00.867 --> 00:20:02.869
- Mr. Hanning...
- What if one of the guys.

304
00:20:03.078 --> 00:20:06.581
what if a marine who was there.
he reads that shit that you made up?

305
00:20:07.791 --> 00:20:11.252
That's why I come down here today.
What if one of the guys sees that?

306
00:20:12.504 --> 00:20:14.089
Man. get him outta my face.

307
00:20:27.727 --> 00:20:32.482
Guy's just off. Off in general.
off his meds. I don't know. but off.

308
00:20:33.358 --> 00:20:36.238
- A lot of them are. I hate to say it...
- Yeah. he puts on a good front.

309
00:20:37.654 --> 00:20:39.614
We'll call the marines.
get a service record.

310
00:20:39.697 --> 00:20:43.576
reach out to some people in his unit.
find out what happened outside of...

311
00:20:43.660 --> 00:20:45.829
- What was it? Fallujah?
- Yeah.

312
00:20:46.830 --> 00:20:49.249
If it went down the way you said.
we'll let it be.

313
00:20:49.916 --> 00:20:53.086
But if not. we'll chalk it up
as a misunderstanding.

314
00:20:53.670 --> 00:20:54.921
But misunderstanding or no.

315
00:20:55.004 --> 00:20:57.882
we will write a correction
if what we printed wasn't accurate.

316
00:21:05.014 --> 00:21:06.641
And we didn't have coffee.

317
00:21:07.976 --> 00:21:09.185
We had chocolate milk.

318
00:21:15.733 --> 00:21:17.485
You miss what you had. though?

319
00:21:18.987 --> 00:21:21.698
I still got too much dog in me
to be settled like that.

320
00:21:24.909 --> 00:21:27.203
It wasn't Cheryl. It was me.

321
00:21:29.581 --> 00:21:32.459
Thing is. is I found a connect
with the boy. you know?

322
00:21:32.917 --> 00:21:35.003
That part of it feels right to me.

323
00:21:35.170 --> 00:21:36.629
Kids are great.

324
00:21:37.464 --> 00:21:38.715
Yeah.

325
00:21:40.383 --> 00:21:44.220
What about you and beadie?
You were quiet there for a time.

326
00:21:46.264 --> 00:21:49.350
Yeah. Bunk once told me
I'm no good for people.

327
00:21:49.434 --> 00:21:51.102
Everyone around me. he said.

328
00:21:52.270 --> 00:21:54.731
- Was he drunk?
- Yeah. But still.

329
00:21:56.900 --> 00:21:59.694
Woman: Omar be dead. I'm tellin' you.
Second woman: Heard that before.

330
00:22:00.069 --> 00:22:01.821
- For real.
- You see him?

331
00:22:01.905 --> 00:22:03.585
Seen his dead ass
layin' right up in there.

332
00:22:03.656 --> 00:22:06.618
Boy up on the corner say
he try to Rob them Koreans and got killed.

333
00:22:20.256 --> 00:22:22.050
You shoulda let me
give him the years. bunk.

334
00:22:22.133 --> 00:22:23.384
He'd have been better off.

335
00:22:25.345 --> 00:22:26.513
Thanks for calling.

336
00:22:26.679 --> 00:22:29.891
Figured you'd wanna see this.
you being so tight with the mope.

337
00:22:35.730 --> 00:22:36.814
Professional job here.

338
00:22:36.898 --> 00:22:40.026
No. I thought so at first.
but the Korean broad we sent downtown

339
00:22:40.151 --> 00:22:44.113
said he got done in by
a short little fella with a big gun.

340
00:22:44.239 --> 00:22:46.574
Shit. walked in an' lit his ass up.

341
00:22:46.783 --> 00:22:48.034
How short?

342
00:22:54.040 --> 00:22:55.250
The boy robbed him?

343
00:22:55.333 --> 00:22:58.169
Counter lady said the hoppers
all ran up in here for souvenirs.

344
00:22:58.628 --> 00:23:02.465
Took his shotty and his semiauto too.
Ran all through his pockets.

345
00:23:05.468 --> 00:23:06.803
Be my guest.

346
00:23:21.109 --> 00:23:22.318
Back on the hunt. were you?

347
00:23:22.986 --> 00:23:27.031
Young 'UN say he out here with no car.
walkin' with a limp an' shit.

348
00:23:27.991 --> 00:23:29.993
He gonna fall. Chris. You gonna see.

349
00:23:35.957 --> 00:23:38.543
- Marlo need a meet.
- For real?

350
00:23:45.008 --> 00:23:46.509
Leander. where we at?

351
00:23:47.051 --> 00:23:49.554
Still setting this up.
Why. did you catch another one?

352
00:23:49.887 --> 00:23:52.724
6:55 and 34.

353
00:23:53.766 --> 00:23:56.185
We're not on anybody yet.
We'll pick it up in the morning.

354
00:23:56.269 --> 00:23:57.687
- All right. later.
- All right.

355
00:23:59.147 --> 00:24:02.066
Okay. Doze. truck. you're on monk metcalf.

356
00:24:02.483 --> 00:24:06.321
Bobby. you and Brian are on Chris partlow.
He usually rides with snoop Pearson.

357
00:24:06.404 --> 00:24:09.032
but if they split.
Karen and Tony will pick up on her.

358
00:24:09.198 --> 00:24:11.618
Marcus. Angela.
you're the backup unit when we need one.

359
00:24:12.076 --> 00:24:13.578
- You're gonna do Stanfield?
- Yeah.

360
00:24:13.870 --> 00:24:17.457
All their business is face-to-face. and
they meet in the open several times a day.

361
00:24:17.665 --> 00:24:20.251
We're just trying to find
the pattern in the meets.

362
00:24:20.460 --> 00:24:21.711
Where do we pick these guys up?

363
00:24:21.878 --> 00:24:24.797
Stanfield has every corner
between mlk and Monroe.

364
00:24:25.006 --> 00:24:28.259
and they start shaping it up
around 11 or so. ok?

365
00:24:28.676 --> 00:24:32.680
That's when the re-up orders start coming
in. when you'll see monk making the rounds.

366
00:24:33.306 --> 00:24:36.267
Most mornings.
marlo starts off with a parley or two

367
00:24:36.351 --> 00:24:39.062
on the playground
between mosher and lanvale.

368
00:24:39.854 --> 00:24:41.606
Now. these guys
seem to be wholesaling. too.

369
00:24:41.689 --> 00:24:43.066
Other dealers. players.

370
00:24:43.149 --> 00:24:46.194
anyone who wants to get with him
gets him there. ok?

371
00:24:46.277 --> 00:24:47.757
Chris and snoop are usually with him.

372
00:24:49.280 --> 00:24:51.240
And mcnulty's got you
covered for papen/vork.

373
00:24:51.658 --> 00:24:54.535
None of what we do here
is necessary for court.

374
00:24:54.619 --> 00:24:57.038
so rest easy on that. all right?

375
00:24:57.955 --> 00:24:59.540
So we stage here tomorrow at nine.

376
00:25:04.712 --> 00:25:08.049
No sign of him. but I ain't on nothin' else
for as long as it take.

377
00:25:08.966 --> 00:25:12.053
You ain't heard? Omar bagged up.

378
00:25:12.720 --> 00:25:14.320
Shit. I thought y'all was gonna tell me.

379
00:25:15.264 --> 00:25:17.058
I just got the word myself from monk.

380
00:25:17.141 --> 00:25:19.060
- Who got him?
- Some young boy.

381
00:25:19.143 --> 00:25:20.728
- Who?
- Ain't heard a name.

382
00:25:20.812 --> 00:25:22.438
Don't even know if there was a why.

383
00:25:23.189 --> 00:25:25.775
Hopper wanna hear a pop.
see the damage. ya know?

384
00:25:26.192 --> 00:25:28.403
Yeah. That shit is gone.

385
00:25:28.569 --> 00:25:30.113
We done with this next resupply.

386
00:25:30.279 --> 00:25:33.074
you an' me got some time
in ac coming to us. don't we?

387
00:25:35.535 --> 00:25:38.371
Forensically. this guy is all over the map.

388
00:25:38.788 --> 00:25:40.957
Sexual to a point. but inhibited.

389
00:25:41.457 --> 00:25:43.876
Nocturnal on some. diurnal on the others.

390
00:25:43.960 --> 00:25:46.170
The notion of targeting the homeless
to begin with?

391
00:25:46.254 --> 00:25:47.964
We've only seen that a couple of times.

392
00:25:48.047 --> 00:25:51.509
but in those instances.
it's been someone within that cohort.

393
00:25:51.968 --> 00:25:55.138
And they're not usually carrying cellphones
and calling newspapers.

394
00:25:55.221 --> 00:25:57.306
You caught a strange one here.

395
00:25:57.515 --> 00:25:59.559
Detectives. Don't get up.

396
00:25:59.642 --> 00:26:02.311
Arthur tolan.
deputy director of the unit.

397
00:26:02.687 --> 00:26:05.565
Just wanted to drop by and make sure
we're progressing your case.

398
00:26:06.149 --> 00:26:08.192
Yeah. Great. Thanks.

399
00:26:08.526 --> 00:26:10.778
You might recognize
the director from television.

400
00:26:10.862 --> 00:26:13.281
- He's done all of them.
- You know those news shows.

401
00:26:13.656 --> 00:26:16.409
Always want a talking head
when a case comes up.

402
00:26:16.492 --> 00:26:20.288
Greta Van susteren.
Nancy grace. Chris Matthews.

403
00:26:20.455 --> 00:26:22.415
that fella with the big forehead.
what's his name?

404
00:26:22.874 --> 00:26:24.834
- Larry king?
- Yeah. yeah. yeah.

405
00:26:25.084 --> 00:26:28.045
What the hell. It's a chance
to get the word out for the bureau.

406
00:26:28.129 --> 00:26:30.173
And I sell some books.

407
00:26:31.966 --> 00:26:35.178
Human hunters - the rise
of the American serial killer.

408
00:26:38.222 --> 00:26:40.558
They've used a lot of my stuff
on those CSI shows.

409
00:26:40.641 --> 00:26:42.477
I've consulted for them.

410
00:26:44.479 --> 00:26:45.688
You haven't heard...

411
00:26:47.148 --> 00:26:49.066
How long you been doing
death investigations?

412
00:26:49.525 --> 00:26:50.818
Eight years.

413
00:26:51.819 --> 00:26:53.863
We don't see a lot
of serial stuff. actually.

414
00:26:54.405 --> 00:26:57.116
Drug murders.
A street robbery every now and then.

415
00:26:57.533 --> 00:26:59.035
300 or so a year.

416
00:26:59.202 --> 00:27:03.039
Well. you've got a serial case now.
so I'll leave you to it.

417
00:27:03.164 --> 00:27:04.207
Good hunting.

418
00:27:05.291 --> 00:27:07.877
Art was lead investigator
on the unabomber thing.

419
00:27:08.044 --> 00:27:10.004
That was. like. 16 years. right?

420
00:27:10.713 --> 00:27:11.714
Yeah.

421
00:27:12.256 --> 00:27:14.300
Then his brother ratted him out?

422
00:27:21.557 --> 00:27:23.142
Homeless is in at 30 inches.

423
00:27:23.893 --> 00:27:25.311
It's good shit there.

424
00:27:26.687 --> 00:27:31.025
No. really. There was a real sense of
place. especially under the Hanover bridge

425
00:27:31.108 --> 00:27:33.402
when the police came up
under there to give the warning.

426
00:27:34.487 --> 00:27:36.489
Drama in small moments like that.

427
00:27:36.948 --> 00:27:39.116
- Truth is. I had a tour guide.
- Yeah?

428
00:27:39.325 --> 00:27:41.327
Yeah. fella I met at a soup kitchen.

429
00:27:41.702 --> 00:27:43.621
Volunteer there. Ex-addict.

430
00:27:44.580 --> 00:27:46.916
There's something about this guy.
I mean. he'sjust...

431
00:27:47.750 --> 00:27:51.420
I don't know. the more he talked. the more I
felt like it was him I wanted to write about.

432
00:27:51.963 --> 00:27:53.422
- Yeah?
- But he's not homeless.

433
00:27:53.506 --> 00:27:56.717
I don't have any peg for him.
Shit. I don't know what the story is.

434
00:27:57.218 --> 00:27:59.095
- He's got a name?
- Reginald cousins.

435
00:27:59.428 --> 00:28:01.490
Volunteers at a soup kitchen.
What's he do for money?

436
00:28:01.514 --> 00:28:04.100
Sells the Baltimore sun
every morning out by light street.

437
00:28:04.392 --> 00:28:08.145
- Shit. Not exactly a growth industry.
- He lives in his sister's basement.

438
00:28:08.229 --> 00:28:11.357
She'll take a plate down to him now
and then but won't let him upstairs.

439
00:28:11.816 --> 00:28:14.902
- Spend some time with him.
- What about the homeless coverage?

440
00:28:15.111 --> 00:28:18.906
You're covered. Take a couple weeks.
see what you see. A'ight?

441
00:28:19.407 --> 00:28:22.869
Late entries from the copshop.
Two dead in a Charles county house fire.

442
00:28:22.952 --> 00:28:25.746
- and a homicide from the city.
- Ettlin. what do we got room for?

443
00:28:25.997 --> 00:28:28.291
We're shy one brief in the Metro digest.

444
00:28:28.457 --> 00:28:29.876
Four paragraphs'll fill.

445
00:28:30.084 --> 00:28:31.294
What's the homicide?

446
00:28:31.919 --> 00:28:35.423
A 34-year-old black male
shot dead in west Baltimore grocery.

447
00:28:35.548 --> 00:28:37.091
Juvenile suspect is being sought.

448
00:28:38.551 --> 00:28:41.637
Write up the fire.
Scratch the murder. we don't have room.

449
00:28:42.513 --> 00:28:44.974
So what we conclude
from a behavioral analysis

450
00:28:45.057 --> 00:28:47.143
of the known forensics is the following.

451
00:28:47.310 --> 00:28:50.521
The suspect is likely a white male.
in his late 20s to late 30s.

452
00:28:50.688 --> 00:28:52.398
He likely is not a college graduate.

453
00:28:52.481 --> 00:28:55.693
but feels nonetheless superior
to those with advanced education.

454
00:28:56.068 --> 00:28:58.905
and he is likely employed
in a bureaucratic entity.

455
00:28:58.988 --> 00:29:01.657
possibly civil service
or quasi-public service.

456
00:29:01.741 --> 00:29:03.200
from which he feels alienated.

457
00:29:03.284 --> 00:29:04.660
He has a problem with authority

458
00:29:04.744 --> 00:29:06.954
and a deep-seated resentment
of those he feels

459
00:29:07.038 --> 00:29:08.998
have impeded his progress professionally.

460
00:29:09.206 --> 00:29:11.417
The minimized sexual activity suggests

461
00:29:11.667 --> 00:29:13.920
that this is not a primary
motive for the killings.

462
00:29:14.295 --> 00:29:18.090
In fact. the bite marks in the last
found victim lacking the DNA of saliva.

463
00:29:18.424 --> 00:29:20.927
indicate to us
possible post-mortem staging.

464
00:29:21.302 --> 00:29:23.429
The suspect has trouble with relationships

465
00:29:23.512 --> 00:29:26.307
and is possibly
a high-functioning alcoholic.

466
00:29:26.515 --> 00:29:29.727
with alcohol being utilized as a trigger
in the commission of these crimes.

467
00:29:29.894 --> 00:29:32.647
His resentment of the homeless
may stem from a relationship

468
00:29:32.730 --> 00:29:36.233
with someone in that cohort.
or his victimization of vagrants

469
00:29:36.317 --> 00:29:38.152
might merely present
an opportunity for him

470
00:29:38.235 --> 00:29:42.198
to assert his superiority
and intellectual prowess.

471
00:29:43.407 --> 00:29:46.202
If you get more. fax it down.
and we can update the profile.

472
00:29:48.412 --> 00:29:51.791
Pa: Special agent Peters.
please call extension 2168.

473
00:29:51.874 --> 00:29:53.584
- Thank you.
- Thanks for everything.

474
00:29:53.668 --> 00:29:54.669
Thanks.

475
00:29:56.504 --> 00:29:57.880
So. what do you think?

476
00:29:58.881 --> 00:29:59.966
