00:44:11.107 --> 00:44:15.403
And certainly. our governor has
in the last year placed severe restrictions

712
00:44:15.487 --> 00:44:18.657
on whatever stopgap state programs
were in place.

713
00:44:19.825 --> 00:44:22.285
And what little remained
of our so-called safety net

714
00:44:22.369 --> 00:44:23.411
was simply shredded.

715
00:44:23.620 --> 00:44:26.331
and more and more of our fellow citizens

716
00:44:26.414 --> 00:44:30.001
found themselves living life
at the broken edges. in the street.

717
00:44:30.836 --> 00:44:34.339
Well. I say that this is not only tragic.
it is unforgivable!

718
00:44:35.924 --> 00:44:38.093
And I am here to say
that no longer can these people

719
00:44:38.176 --> 00:44:40.428
with whom I share this stage tonight
be invisible.

720
00:44:40.929 --> 00:44:45.141
just... just as all of those
without shelter in this city.

721
00:44:45.225 --> 00:44:48.311
in this country.
can no longer be invisible to us.

722
00:44:48.603 --> 00:44:50.981
And it is regrettable
that it has taken the actions

723
00:44:51.064 --> 00:44:53.358
of a remorseless
predator to make us reflect.

724
00:44:53.441 --> 00:44:55.777
But we in Baltimore have been tested.

725
00:44:56.027 --> 00:44:58.738
and we have been taught
that all of our citizens

726
00:44:58.822 --> 00:45:01.241
deserve the full protection of the law.

727
00:45:01.575 --> 00:45:05.161
and the full support of the community.

728
00:45:05.245 --> 00:45:07.038
We are saying to this senseless killer.

729
00:45:07.122 --> 00:45:12.043
and to all the other ills that prey on
those without shelter in our city.

730
00:45:12.794 --> 00:45:14.379
not tonight can you prey on them.

731
00:45:14.504 --> 00:45:18.133
And not tomorrow. Not any longer.

732
00:45:18.258 --> 00:45:19.258
Crowd: No!

733
00:45:19.301 --> 00:45:21.386
We will protect you!

734
00:45:22.971 --> 00:45:23.972
Thank you.

735
00:46:04.179 --> 00:46:06.514
She asked you keep that one stirred.

736
00:46:09.684 --> 00:46:11.394
You were on my thing. right?

737
00:46:12.270 --> 00:46:14.522
I guess I owe you a drink on that.
What's your poison?

738
00:46:14.773 --> 00:46:17.359
I'm okay. senator.
thank you very much.

739
00:46:18.693 --> 00:46:21.196
Obonda. huh? That's a good one.

740
00:46:22.614 --> 00:46:25.200
You know. that was mostly my evidence
you beat back there. right?

741
00:46:25.367 --> 00:46:28.745
- You think you could do that again?
- Excuse me?

742
00:46:29.287 --> 00:46:31.581
Except this time.
the jury's a federal one.

743
00:46:31.665 --> 00:46:33.833
Say. nine white. three black.

744
00:46:35.377 --> 00:46:37.462
Time for you to tip on out. detective.

745
00:46:41.549 --> 00:46:43.635
Bank records on that mortgage application

746
00:46:43.718 --> 00:46:46.388
you made on the calvert county
property years back.

747
00:46:46.930 --> 00:46:49.683
Now. why don't you
take that back to Billy Murphy?

748
00:46:49.766 --> 00:46:51.935
Ask your attorney
what you're exposed to.

749
00:46:52.686 --> 00:46:56.815
At this point. this is just between
us two gentlemen here. senator.

750
00:46:58.525 --> 00:47:00.235
And no one else till I make it so.

751
00:47:00.735 --> 00:47:05.240
What? You tryin' to sell a case back to me?
Motherfucker. if you don't get...

752
00:47:05.365 --> 00:47:06.908
I don't get paid like that.

753
00:47:07.450 --> 00:47:10.537
I get paid when I come back
in a couple nights' time with questions

754
00:47:10.620 --> 00:47:14.165
and you. sir. have answers. or my next call
will be to the us attorney's office.

755
00:47:14.290 --> 00:47:16.793
and we will go again. but for real.

756
00:47:17.627 --> 00:47:20.088
You can keep that copy. Ma'am.

757
00:47:32.934 --> 00:47:37.272
Just to let you know. before
the fireworks start. I'm spiking this lead.

758
00:47:37.439 --> 00:47:39.774
- But you got my back?
- As best I can.

759
00:47:41.234 --> 00:47:42.235
Scott.

760
00:47:56.374 --> 00:47:57.500
I'm spiking your lead.

761
00:48:00.211 --> 00:48:02.630
I'm not running a story
about a public gathering.

762
00:48:03.006 --> 00:48:05.383
a candlelight vigil at city hall. in fact.

763
00:48:05.467 --> 00:48:08.845
where the lead anecdote and quote
is from an unnamed homeless woman.

764
00:48:09.179 --> 00:48:11.973
She doesn't want to be known as homeless.
I explained that.

765
00:48:12.307 --> 00:48:15.018
Scott. there were hundreds
of homeless down there tonight.

766
00:48:15.810 --> 00:48:18.063
People who voluntarily
attended this event.

767
00:48:18.480 --> 00:48:22.108
And I'd guess that any number of them
would've let you put their names in the paper.

768
00:48:22.734 --> 00:48:24.903
But her story is great.
Look at that quote.

769
00:48:24.986 --> 00:48:27.322
It's a perfect quote.
Best quote I could ever ask for.

770
00:48:27.530 --> 00:48:29.032
That's my concern at this point.

771
00:48:31.993 --> 00:48:33.161
Jesus Christ.

772
00:48:34.454 --> 00:48:36.414
To hell with you if you think I made it up.

773
00:48:38.249 --> 00:48:42.253
We have a standard that we follow here.
I'm gonna follow it.

774
00:49:10.323 --> 00:49:11.866
Here it comes. Gus.

775
00:49:21.000 --> 00:49:24.170
Gus. you're retopping Scott's vigil copy?

776
00:49:24.337 --> 00:49:26.506
- I am.
- But I thought...

777
00:49:26.589 --> 00:49:29.551
Anonymous attribution in a public setting.
There's no need for it.

778
00:49:30.552 --> 00:49:33.096
- Gus. let's discuss this.
- Actually. I did discuss it

779
00:49:33.179 --> 00:49:35.306
with the Metro editor. and he agrees.

780
00:49:35.890 --> 00:49:37.600
Now. the story's on the copy desk.

781
00:49:37.851 --> 00:49:40.603
and as a line editor working this story.
I feel I've done my job.

782
00:49:41.688 --> 00:49:45.066
Now. you as the me.
if you want to go another way.

783
00:49:45.483 --> 00:49:46.923
you pull the story back and re-edit.

784
00:49:47.235 --> 00:49:49.529
But we have a sourcing policy here.
and I know it.

785
00:49:49.737 --> 00:49:52.448
and I do not feel comfortable
bending the rules in this instance.

786
00:49:52.532 --> 00:49:53.533
Good night.

787
00:50:13.469 --> 00:50:14.512
Yeah?

788
00:50:14.929 --> 00:50:16.598
Mcnulty. it's christeson.

789
00:50:16.764 --> 00:50:19.475
Listen. my case is down
an' I wanted to thank you.

790
00:50:19.559 --> 00:50:21.352
I couldn't have done it othennise.

791
00:50:21.895 --> 00:50:22.979
No problem.

792
00:50:36.492 --> 00:50:39.078
- Hey. it went great.
- Kids asleep?

793
00:50:39.162 --> 00:50:41.206
Yeah. but they saw you on wbal.

794
00:50:41.289 --> 00:50:42.790
Anna said your hair looked funny.

795
00:50:43.208 --> 00:50:45.168
Well. just so long as she was impressed.

796
00:50:45.627 --> 00:50:46.711
CNN was there.

797
00:50:46.961 --> 00:50:49.130
I wonder if they'll cycle
any coverage through tonight.

798
00:50:49.422 --> 00:50:51.799
- A good day for hizzoner. huh?
- I don't know.

799
00:50:52.008 --> 00:50:54.052
Nerese shook me down
for a mayoral endorsement.

800
00:50:54.135 --> 00:50:56.387
and Clay Davis. back from the grave.

801
00:50:56.471 --> 00:50:58.139
took a couple of liquor board seats.

802
00:50:58.598 --> 00:51:02.310
Just so as they won'tjoin in
upshaw's war party in prince George's.

803
00:51:02.644 --> 00:51:05.480
You're gonna endorse nerese?
You told me you prefer bond.

804
00:51:05.939 --> 00:51:08.483
I do. but this thing with upshaw...

805
00:51:08.733 --> 00:51:11.903
Shit. I might even have to give him a bump
just to calm him down.

806
00:51:11.986 --> 00:51:13.780
God. What's he asking?

807
00:51:14.322 --> 00:51:17.617
- There. Look.
- What's upshaw asking?

808
00:51:18.076 --> 00:51:21.037
Half of any extra school
or anti-crime money

809
00:51:21.120 --> 00:51:23.831
I get outta the legislature for Baltimore
would go to pg county.

810
00:51:24.499 --> 00:51:28.169
You take that deal and Baltimore's out half
of what you want to bring back to the schools.

811
00:51:28.253 --> 00:51:31.714
Yeah. but if I don't win. Jen.
I bring back exactly nothing.

812
00:51:32.840 --> 00:51:33.841
Look.

813
00:51:34.384 --> 00:51:36.970
Carcetti on TV: And we are saying
to this senseless killer.

814
00:51:37.053 --> 00:51:38.346
and to all the other ills...

815
00:51:49.440 --> 00:51:50.650
Go on. Straight to bed.

816
00:51:50.733 --> 00:51:52.610
- Hey. kiddo.
- Hey. mcnulty.

817
00:51:55.238 --> 00:51:56.406
Where'd you go to?

818
00:51:57.699 --> 00:51:59.450
None of your business really. Jimmy.

819
00:51:59.993 --> 00:52:01.512
And next time. I'm not going anywhere.

820
00:52:01.536 --> 00:52:04.956
Next time. you're gonna be out on your ass.
because that's my fucking house.

821
00:52:13.548 --> 00:52:14.632
That's police work. son.

822
00:52:15.008 --> 00:52:17.302
I pull the adc book to find a location.

823
00:52:17.552 --> 00:52:20.179
and I'm on the same page number
as the second hand.

824
00:52:20.263 --> 00:52:23.016
And I remember we had
a lotta clocks with 34 seconds.

825
00:52:23.141 --> 00:52:24.541
That's the page for west Baltimore.

826
00:52:24.726 --> 00:52:28.229
Right. Now. the second hand
is always the map page.

827
00:52:28.730 --> 00:52:31.232
Longitude. a-through-k. is the hour.

828
00:52:31.399 --> 00:52:34.819
and for the latitude.
they go by five-minute intervals.

829
00:52:35.653 --> 00:52:37.697
Now. they know
the meeting spot in advance.

830
00:52:37.822 --> 00:52:40.366
- and they code it by the grid square.
- Hmm.

831
00:52:40.658 --> 00:52:42.660
But if the clock
has nothing to do with time.

832
00:52:43.161 --> 00:52:44.412
how do they know when to meet?

833
00:52:50.460 --> 00:52:55.089
Everything's less than
a half hour of driving. even in traffic.

834
00:52:57.884 --> 00:52:59.552
My guess is that the standing logic

835
00:52:59.635 --> 00:53:02.138
is that they meet within an hour or so.

836
00:53:08.102 --> 00:53:10.104
You know what else makes sense?

837
00:53:12.523 --> 00:53:15.109
This clock face when no one
was on the move?

838
00:53:17.278 --> 00:53:19.530
The times are all at 35 seconds.

839
00:53:20.281 --> 00:53:22.617
And that's the page for east bawlmer.

840
00:53:23.868 --> 00:53:26.412
- Cheese.
- Cheese wagstaff?

841
00:53:32.710 --> 00:53:36.214
Marlo's wholesaling on the westside through
monk. and on the eastside with cheese.

842
00:53:36.297 --> 00:53:39.675
- He's got the whole goddamn city.
- How do we know it's cheese?

843
00:53:47.975 --> 00:53:49.102
You. too. huh?

844
00:53:51.646 --> 00:53:53.731
- You all are good with this?
- Kima.

845
00:53:54.690 --> 00:53:55.691
Not me.

846
00:54:01.322 --> 00:54:04.325
All the guys at the
bar. Jimmy. all the girls.

847
00:54:05.368 --> 00:54:06.994
they don't show up at your wake.

848
00:54:07.453 --> 00:54:08.996
Not because they don't like you

849
00:54:09.622 --> 00:54:12.041
but because they never knew your last name.

850
00:54:12.667 --> 00:54:15.461
A month later. someone tells 'em.
"oh. Jimmy died."

851
00:54:15.545 --> 00:54:18.047
"Jimmy who?" "Jimmy the cop."

852
00:54:18.297 --> 00:54:21.050
"Oh." they say. "Him."

853
00:54:22.009 --> 00:54:23.344
And all the people on the job.

854
00:54:24.637 --> 00:54:27.515
all the people you spent
all those hours in the radio car with.

855
00:54:27.640 --> 00:54:30.184
the guys with their feet up
on their desk telling stories.

856
00:54:30.685 --> 00:54:34.397
who shorted you on the food runs.
who signed your overtime slips.

857
00:54:34.939 --> 00:54:37.859
In the end. they're not
gonna be there either.

858
00:54:39.193 --> 00:54:42.530
Family. That's it. Family.
and if you're lucky.

859
00:54:43.030 --> 00:54:45.324
one or two friends
who are the same as family.

860
00:54:47.160 --> 00:54:50.329
That's all the best of us get.
Everything else is just...

861
00:54:59.255 --> 00:55:01.048
There is no serial killer.

862
00:55:03.551 --> 00:55:05.678
There are no murders. I made it all up.

863
00:55:11.976 --> 00:55:14.645
They... they were shutting us down.
They were just...

864
00:55:15.813 --> 00:55:17.023
It's hard to explain.

865
00:55:17.106 --> 00:55:20.401
I don't even know where the anger comes
from. I don't know how to make it stop.

866
00:55:22.195 --> 00:55:24.155
They fucking task me. they do.

867
00:55:29.368 --> 00:55:31.579
We took the money from
the bullshit investigation.

868
00:55:31.662 --> 00:55:32.914
rerouted it to Lester.

869
00:55:33.206 --> 00:55:35.666
Now he's got the cake
to take down marlo Stanfield.

870
00:55:38.002 --> 00:55:41.297
And now that I've done all this.
now that I've watched myself do it.

871
00:55:41.380 --> 00:55:42.757
I can't even stand to...

872
00:55:47.637 --> 00:55:48.930
Lester says he's close.

873
00:55:49.764 --> 00:55:52.391
Time will pass. and I'll be able
to shut this thing down.

874
00:55:55.645 --> 00:55:56.729
If you don't go to jail.

875
00:56:03.027 --> 00:56:04.529
You had no fucking right.

876
00:56:04.946 --> 00:56:07.114
- I know.
- This is my life. too.

877
00:56:10.952 --> 00:56:13.112
You start to tell the story.
you think you're the hero.

